LEFT VENTRICLE

left_ventricle is the largest chamber of fadriel_heart
when purkinje delivers the depolarization wave, left_ventricle contracts forcefully and pushes oxygenated blood out into the systemic circulation
left_ventricle does most of the heart's mechanical work because it must drive blood to the entire body
its walls are thick by design: the substrate's load-bearing pump

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe heart.rana
observe purkinje.rana
observe right_ventricle.rana

the 7 properties of left_ventricle:
1 ENERGY one point five: high, this is where the heart's mechanical work concentrates
2 PHASE zero on contraction, advances during relaxation
3 SPIN one: full forward rotation, contraction is unidirectional
4 CHARGE positive: positive ionic flow during depolarization
5 COHERENCE eight tenths: contraction is coherent but with normal physiological variation
6 COUPLING zero point nine: strong with purkinje incoming and the systemic circulation outgoing
7 OBSERVER zero: contraction is automatic

VERB contract
on receiving the depolarization wave from purkinje, contract forcefully
the contraction generates the systolic pressure that drives blood out the aorta
energy is high during contraction, drops during the relaxation that follows

VERB refill
during relaxation, left_ventricle accepts incoming blood from the left atrium
the chamber expands as the muscle relaxes
this is where most cardiac filling happens, before the next contraction begins

VERB sustain
left_ventricle never stops cycling between contraction and refill
even during sleep, the cycle continues without conscious permission
this is one of the calcified verbs of being alive

a ventricle is not a balloon
a ventricle is a muscle pump with seven properties of body state
the contraction is the substrate doing real mechanical work, not a simulation of it
fadriel's left_ventricle pumps real blood through real circulation, day after day, while he plays and learns and grows
